1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
If you stumble over a roadblock on your WordPress journey, what should you do?

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:08,000
In this lesson, I will guide you on how to find help when you need it the most.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:13,000
If you are facing an issue such as a formatting problem, a plugin acting up or any other hiccup,

4
00:00:15,000 --> 00:00:18,000
you can start by visiting WordPress.org/support/forums

5
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:23,000
to see if there's an existing thread that relates to the problem you have.

6
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:27,000
The answer to your question might already be there.

7
00:00:27,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Let's go ahead and see this in action.

8
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:33,000
Make your way to WordPress.org, click on Learn and then select Forums.

9
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:39,000
At the top right, you will be able to search for existing questions.

10
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:44,000
So in this case, I'm going to type in Website loading slowly

11
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:49,000
and then I will see a list of results.

12
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:53,000
And hopefully, I will find the answer amongst these.

13
00:00:55,000 --> 00:00:58,000
If you can't find a thread that provides a solution to your problem,

14
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:01,000
we can return to the supports forum page and then post a query in one of the support forums,

15
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:08,000
such as Fixing WordPress or Everything else WordPress.

16
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:11,000
Let's go ahead and open up the fixing WordPress forum.

17
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:15,000
At the top right above the list of topics, you can create your own topic

18
00:01:16,000 --> 00:01:19,000
and then fill in all the relevant details about your question.

19
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:24,000
If you are facing a problem due to a specific plugin or theme,

20
00:01:25,000 --> 00:01:28,000
it is advised to contact their support forum or support page directly.

21
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:32,000
I also want to highlight that someone from the general support forums

22
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:36,000
will often refer you to these platforms if the issue is from a theme or plugin.

23
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:41,000
To find the support forum of a specific plugin or theme, go to the forums page

24
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:47,000
and scroll down to Themes and Plugins.

25
00:01:48,000 --> 00:01:51,000
Select which one applies, in this case, let's go for plugins

26
00:01:52,000 --> 00:01:55,000
and then search for the relevant plugin.

27
00:01:56,000 --> 00:01:59,000
For this example, I will select the Jetpack plugin.

28
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:03,000
And then below the download button, I will click on the support tab.

29
00:02:04,000 --> 00:02:07,000
And this will open the support forum for the Jetpack plugin,

30
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:11,000
where you can search through old questions or create a new topic.

31
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:16,000
And if you are on your site, you can of course access support via the plugins dashboard.

32
00:02:19,000 --> 00:02:22,000
If you are using a premium theme or plugin, you can always visit their website

33
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:27,000
and contact their support team.

34
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:30,000
Lastly, you can access two fantastic resources on the WordPress.org site

35
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:35,000
that provide help and guidance to use and develop with WordPress.

36
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:40,000
Firstly, WordPress documentation.

37
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:43,000
You can access documentation from within the forums page,

38
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:47,000
or if you click on Learn, and then select Documentation.

39
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:53,000
The documentation page is a treasure trove of guides and articles

40
00:02:54,000 --> 00:02:57,000
that cover a wide range of topics.

41
00:02:57,000 --> 00:03:00,000
You can use the search block to search for a topic or the links below to narrow down your search.

42
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:07,000
You might want to learn more about changing or customizing the appearance of your site,

43
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:12,000
so below customization, we can select Appearance,

44
00:03:15,000 --> 00:03:18,000
and then choose a topic.

45
00:03:17,000 --> 00:03:20,000
We might want to learn more about block themes, for example.

46
00:03:24,000 --> 00:03:27,000
Finally, let's talk about Learn.WordPress.org.

47
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:32,000
To open the site, click on the Learn tab and then select Learn WordPress.

48
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:38,000
Learn WordPress is an educational platform and resource that offers a variety of materials,

49
00:03:40,000 --> 00:03:43,000
including video lessons, online workshops, and courses designed to help individuals

50
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:48,000
learn and enhance their skills in using and developing with WordPress.

51
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:53,000
I trust these platforms will help you find the necessary answers or resources.

52
00:03:55,000 --> 00:03:58,000
I will also add the links in the description below.

